The paper discusses machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are core topics in computer science. The use of smart contracts and blockchain technology also suggests a focus on distributed computing and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses financial and gamified incentive structures, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
